e finite sized nucleus. Combining the dewar constraints\nwith BBN, we exclude for the first time a cross section above $10^{-26} \\text{\ncm}^{2}$ for DM mass 0.8-5.5 GeV, for any sign interaction. One DM model that\nis constrained is sexaquark $(uuddss)$ DM with mass $m_X \\sim 2$ GeV; it\nremains viable.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Dec 2021 18:34:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-02"}
