cate that\nthe $f(R)$ Starobinsky model provides a good fit to the currently available\ndata for a set of values of its parameters, being, therefore, a possible\nalternative to the $\\Lambda$CDM model.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Dec 2021 20:44:37 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 3 Jun 2022 19:09:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-07"}
