o-dimensional incommensurate state\nwhere Mn ordered moments are aligned in the $ab$ plane. A possible origin for\nthe different AFM states in the systems was discussed. Both CaMn$_2$As$_2$ and\nSrMn$_2$As$_2$ show very large anisotropy in the nuclear spin-lattice\nrelaxation rate 1/$T_1$ in the paramagnetic state. 1/$T_1$ for $H$ $||$ $ab$ is\nmuch larger than that for $H$ $|| $c$, indicating strong anisotropic AFM spin\nfluctuations in both compounds.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Dec 2021 21:27:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-10"}
