, including low-voltage fast activity, can be captured by the\nindependent component analysis of scalp EEG. The visibility of the ictal\nactivity strongly depends on the depth of the sources. The equivalent current\ndipole localization can point to the seizure onset zone (SOZ) with an accuracy\nthat can be as high as 10mm for superficially located sources, that gradually\ndecreases for deeper seizure generators, averaging at 47 mm in the 8 analyzed\npatients. Independent component analysis is therefore shown to have a promising\nSOZ localizing value, indicating whether the seizure onset zone is neocortical,\nand its approximate location, or located in mesial structures. That may\ncontribute to a better crafting of the hypotheses used as basis of the\nstereo-EEG implantations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 2 Dec 2021 10:13:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-03"}
