es with $Re$ in zero-pressure-gradient (ZPG)\nTBLs, this effect becomes accentuated by the APG. Despite the reduction of the\nouter TKE production at higher Reynolds numbers, the mechanisms of energization\nof large scales are still present.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 2 Dec 2021 15:32:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 4 Mar 2022 16:06:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-07"}
